AdCreator  - ability to create ads from text and images
https://github.com/koseime/AdCreator.git


Create an ad from parts
usage: 
	./kosei-ad-creator {options}
options: 
	-o <output directory> : bulk - Output directory name
	-i <input file>  : bulk - Input file to bulk process ads format:[id<tab><image path><description>
	-x <eXecution type>  : bulk or single
	-p <product image>  : single - product image
	-d <ad text>  : single - ad text
	-r <ad result>  : single - ad result output



example single use:
./kosei-ad-creator -x single -p ./images/vacuum1.jpg -d "Here is a jpg" -r output/out-single.png

example bulk use:
./kosei-ad-creator -x bulk -o ./output -i ./samples/sample.tsv -g ./images


Required libraries (linux):
sudo yum install SDL-static.x86_64
sudo yum install cairo-devel
sudo yum install libjpeg-turbo-static

Required libraries (mac):
brew install pkg-config
brew install SDL
brew install cario
Note: may ask you to install XQuartz: https://xquartz.macosforge.org


Required for ImageMagick
$wget http://www.imagemagick.org/download/ImageMagick.tar.gz ./
$tar -xvzf ImageMagick.tar.gz 
$cd ImageMagick-6.8.9-5/
$./configure
$make
$sudo make install




You will need to download the hadoop source for pipes to work:
wget https://archive.apache.org/dist/hadoop/core/hadoop-2.2.0/hadoop-2.2.0-src.tar.gz


To make on commandline for pipes:
HADOOP_SRC=<path to the untarred hadoop-2.2.0-src directory from above> make -f makefile.pipes
 
To make in eclipse, you will need to set a couple of env variables:
Project->Properties->C/C++ Build/Environment ->
	PATH   $PATH:/usr/local/bin     //NOTE: this is to be able to find the sdl-config  and pkg-config execs for the build
	HADOOP_SRC   <path to the untarred hadoop-2.2.0-src directory from above>



